args:
The party attempts to build a gate to save the
world from destruction, but needs Alfonse's
power to complete it. Having discovered the
fortress where he's being held, the party
launches an operation to rescue him.
I'm sorry, Sharena. We were so close\nto getting your brother, but...
It wasn't your fault. Even our combined\nstrength wasn't enough to save him.
Perhaps I am the one who should\napologize. My intervention seems to\nhave warped history in no small way.
It appears I was wrong to challenge you\nas I did, Prince {player_name}.
No, Prince Chrom. Were I in your position,\nI'd likely have done the same thing.
And you were right to be concerned.\nAfter all, we just saw the Empress use\nthe power of the Other to seal the rifts.
Now I understand why the other world's\nversion of me would seek to harness it.
I respect your forthrightness about that\ndespite knowing my concerns.
I see little point in hiding it.\nBut I will make good use of your warning.
You said my choices here might bring\nabout the end of the world, and that's\nsomething I intend to take to heart.
Don't worry, pal. We'll make sure the\nsituation never even gets to that point.\nYou ain't gotta lift a finger!
Heh. Perhaps I should put more faith\nin the strength of the bonds you share.
But remember this: If you were to\nsacrifice yourself, that action could\nend up causing great harm to others.
Well, I suppose that's that.\nOh, except for that one little issue...
I haven't forgotten that the Other\nis still holding Alfonse, Sharena.

It's only a matter of time before she tries
to use his power, so we have until that
moment to come up with some sort of
countermeasure.
Actually, Princess Zethia has given me a\nplan that may help resolve the situation.
Yes. Her idea was to build a gate.
It would require a different sort of gate\nthan the kind that exists on your world,\nPrincess Sharena. But yes, she thought so.
I imagine the idea is that if the lack of\na gate has made our world unstable,\nbuilding one would stabilize it?
It makes sense in theory, but how does\none BUILD a gate?
I believe it to be possible. Three hundred\nyears ago, in fact, the Dyrenell Empire\nattempted essentially the same thing.
The materials remain within the Halidom.\nPerhaps we can finish the gate they\nwere trying to create three centuries ago.
Well, THIS is exciting! Let's do it!
And so, we set to work on saving the world\nfrom impending destruction.
Teams were formed to research the construction\nof the gate, track where Alfonse had been\ntaken, and deal with the opened rifts.
With no shortage of tasks to occupy us,\nthe days flew by in an instant...
You seem exhausted, Cleo. Maybe it's\na good idea to rest for a bit?
Out of the question when another mass\nopening of rifts could occur at any time.

And how exactly would we stop it
if you've collapsed from exhaustion?
I know you're making good progress,
so there's no need to push it.

Yes, I feel the end is in sight, but...
Well, without insight from someone who
knows more about the gate than I do,
I don't see how we'll ever get there.
Sharena has seen plenty of gates,\nhasn't she?
Well, I may have experience USING gates,\nbut BUILDING them is a whole other thing.
My brother would know more, but...
You're probably right—I was always\nimpressed by how smart he was.
I feel like we're talking in circles here.\nWould it be better if Alfonse was here?\nOf course. But he's NOT.
On the matter of Prince Alfonse's\nwhereabouts, I may have an idea.\nIt's a slim hope to be sure, but...
I don't know if I'd call it that, exactly...
I'm trying to recall what I heard about the\nplace Prince {player_name} was\nbeing held on the world I first visited.
Apparently he was being forced to watch\nthe world's end from that particular spot.
I believe it was a Dyrenell Empire fortress\nthat was also a research facility?
That could be worth investigating.\nLet's check it out!
Duuuude, we found the fortress\nChrom was talking about!
Alas, it's crawling with soldiers, and there\nis a rather foreboding vibe to the place.
It's in an area that hasn't seen any conflict\nin quite some time, which makes it odd to\nsee its guards at such high alert.
That means there must be\nsomething important there!

It sounds like there's a real chance
Prince Alfonse is being held there.
Er, but we can't very well just walk up
to the front door and knock.
So long as they're holding Prince Alfonse\nhostage, the options are rather limited.\nDiscretion must be our watchword.
Well, if I just turn into a dragon and go\n＂raawwwrr!＂ all those soldiers will come\nchasing after me, right?
Decoys are a tried and true method,\nbut we cannot permit you to endanger\nyourself in such a way.
Guys, I'm a dragon. A DIVINE dragon.\nI'll be fiiiine!
It's certainly a better idea than us just\nstanding around wringing our little hands.
But if you're worried about Tiki, I'll go too.\nI'm confident they won't be able to handle\nTWO rampaging dragons!
All right—but I need both of you to\npromise that you won't expose yourselves\nto any unnecessary danger.
Dragons! Dragons on the attack!\nProtect the fort at all cost!\nDon't let them get near it!
Hurry, we need to find Prince Alfonse\nwhile they're busy chasing dragons!
There are still soldiers in the fortress.\nWe have to be careful.
If we don't find Prince Alfonse soon,\nthis will all be for nothing!
Ah, hell. This ain't good, boss.\nI think they've been expectin' us.
Look out at the northern plain!
The imperial army... Damn!\nThis whole thing is an ambush!

Yeah, sure looks like it—but that means
they've fallen into OUR ambush, too!
...Quick! Alert the folks what are
waitin' back in the woods!
It's gonna be a real grind, but we gotta\ntake this fortress and protect it at the\nsame time!
Right! Keep the soldiers outside away from\nthe fort while we claim it from within.\nWe can do this! Let's go!
